The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, August 13, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Tokyo, Aug. 12: Two of Japans biggest banking groups, UFJ Holdings and Mitsubishi Tokyo Financial Group, have reached a basic agreement to merge to create the worlds largest bank by October 1, 2005. The merged entity will be called Mitsubishi UFJ Holdings, Inc.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 12: The countrys industrial growth touched 7.6 per cent in the first quarter of this fiscal against 5.7 per cent in the year-ago period, according to quick estimates of the index of industrial production.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 12: Global steel major Groupe Arcelor, with a turnover of 26 billion euro, is eyeing the Indian market. It is in talks with various manufacturers for both cash and equity partnership.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 12: Delhi High Court today rejected the plea of D. S. Pendse, former MD of Tata Finance, for lifting six months stipulation for completing the trial in a case related to violation of Sebi norms.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 12: The value-added tax regime, which comes into force from April 2005, signals the end of the inspection raj, committee chairman Asim Dasgupta said today.
